Day 6 of Our Alaskan Cruise- Ketchikan, Alaska with the Saxman Village in the Morning and The Great Alaskan Lumberjack Show in the Afternoon

At the dock in Ketchikan, Alaska. That's another cruise ship parked right behind us.
The life preserver picture of Johnnie and Obie in Ketchikan, Alaska
Jonobie and Jeff do their picture

Saxman Village- a Tingit village, 3 miles S of Ketchikan on Tongass Narrows
Totem poles with lodge house in the background. Totem poles were moved from abandoned towns and cemeteries of the Tlingit. See the excellent book by Garfield and Forrest. 'The Wolf and the Raven' (isbn 0-295-73998-3) for descriptions of these totem poles.
Oops- a threat of rain. Ketchikan receives 15 FEET of rain a year!

Doesn't look good
Pictures of the Saxman dancers are blurred as they were being taken without our flash working!
